'''Tsunou Shrine''' (つのうじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Takashima|Q845794|WD=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}.

=== History ===
The founding date is unknown. There are two Tsunou Shrines in Imazu-chō, Takashima City; both the shrine in Imazu-chō Kita-gyō and the one in Imazu-chō Tsunokawa are regarded as descendant shrines of Tsunou Shrine in {{ill|lt=Takashima District (Shiga)|Q11669692|WD=Q11669692|lt=Takashima District|1=Takashima District, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Ōmi Province|Q843882|WD=Q843882|1=Ōmi Province}}, listed in the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|WD=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}.

=== Imazu-chō Kita-gyō ===
It is said to have been invited by Kadono Omi no Kishi no Sukune, sixth-generation grandson of {{ill|lt=Ki no Tsuno|Q11605107|WD=Q11605107|lt=Ki no Tsuno Sukune-no-Kami|1=Ki no Tsuno}}. It was the {{ill|lt=sōsha|Q1107129|WD=Q1107129|lt=sōsha|1=Sōja shrine}} of Tsunou-go and Kawakami-go. In the {{ill|lt=Sengoku period (Japan)|Q204023|WD=Q204023|lt=Sengoku period|1=Sengoku period}}, the shrine buildings burned down in warfare, but were rebuilt in {{ill|lt=Hōei|Q1145262|WD=Q1145262|1=Hōei}} 1 ({{ill|lt=1704|Q6824|WD=Q6824|1=1704}}). It became a {{ill|lt=gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}} in {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|WD=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 14 ({{ill|lt=1881|Q7808|WD=Q7808|1=1881}}). It enshrines {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Tsunogori Mitama-no-Kami|1=UNKNOWN}} and Ki no Tsuno Sukune-no-Kami as principal deities, with {{ill|lt=Takeuchi no Sukune|Q1073668|WD=Q1073668|lt=Takeuchi Ōomi|1=Takenouchi no Sukune}} (Takeuchi Sukune) as associated deity.

=== Imazu-chō Tsunokawa ===
Like the Kita-gyō Tsunou Shrine, its shrine buildings were burned in warfare in the Sengoku period. It became a {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|WD=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}} in Meiji 9 ({{ill|lt=1876|Q7766|WD=Q7766|1=1876}}). It enshrines {{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi|Q276944|WD=Q276944|lt=Ōkuninushi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōkuninushi}} and {{ill|lt=Takeuchi no Sukune|Q1073668|WD=Q1073668|1=Takenouchi no Sukune}}.

=== Precinct shrines ===
* Imazu-chō Kita-gyō: Tabe Shrine ({{ill|lt=Ōkuninushi|Q276944|WD=Q276944|lt=Ōkuninushi Ōkami|1=Ōkuninushi}}), Inari-sha ({{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|1=Ukanomitama}}, {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōta-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}, {{ill|lt=Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōmiyahime-no-Mikoto}}), Itsukushima-sha ({{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q11059454|lt=Ichikishimahime-no-Mikoto|1=Ichikishima-hime}}, {{ill|lt=Tagorihime-no-Mikoto|UNKNOWN|lt=Tagorihime-no-Mikoto}}), Kitano-sha ({{ill|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|Q382005|WD=Q382005|lt=Sugawara no Michizane-kō|1=Sugawara no Michizane}})
** Tabe Shrine is a candidate for Tabe Shrine in Takashima District, Ōmi Province, listed in the Engishiki Jinmyōchō
* Imazu-chō Tsunokawa: Sannō Ōmiya

